    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian" kindref="compound">Laplacian</ref> to smoothly deform a region preserving mesh fine details. How to use:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Initialize <ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian" kindref="compound">Laplacian</ref> for the region being deformed, here region properties are remembered.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Change positions of some vertices within the region and call fixVertex for them.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Optionally call <ref refid="group__GeneralGroup_1gaed49a7865f3de5ad169b768e09d8d91a" kindref="member">updateSolver()</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Call <ref refid="group__GeneralGroup_1ga13fee62f9942597d173e9f43fe75c60e" kindref="member">apply()</ref> to change the remaining vertices within the region Then steps 1-4 or 2-4 can be repeated. <programlisting filename="cpp-samples/LaplacianDeformation.cpp"></programlisting> </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
